<br>
With a 10ac 15ac 25ac 54 ac shield I found the following to be true:<br>
For everey 10ac of the shield you mitigate an additional 1% of the damage taken while shielding somebody. So, for example, if Enchanter-A is getting hit for 100 damage and I shield them they will take 50 damage and I will take 75 damage without a shield equipped. If I equip my 54ac shield I now take 70damage instead of 75 (the damage is rounded up unless you are gonna round to over 75% damage then it's rounded down).<br>
<br>
Personally I find this rule to be kinda lackluser, as I was literally expecting to at least knock about 0.75-1% damage off for every 2ac of my shield to a maximum of 25% damage mitigated (leaving me with taking only 50% /shield damage, keeping the mob from doing less overall damage than they would be doing on one target anyway).<br>
<br>
Maybe we will see some warr-only shields with more than 54ac in the future, because at this rate it is gonna take a 250ac shield to keep the mobs overall damage at 100% (50/50) without allowing them to actually do up to 25% more damage than they should be doing without you /shielding someone. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=160002"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home1.gte.net/res00jhn/gnimtag.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khumak>Khumak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/13/02 2:04:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2504.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: /shield</span><hr size=1> Good to know.  I had been wondering what effect shields would have on mitigation while using /shield.  I don't see myself ever using a shield (don't even own one) so it's probably a moot point unless something changes drastically about the way shields work or they put some insane shields in the game. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=85547">Khumak</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
